dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.address.InterfaceNetworkAddressDetails
dataStructure.description:
This class defines the semantics of how this NetworkAddress is contained in this particular DeviceInterface.

This association class is optional
dataStructure.label: InterfaceNetworkAddressDetails

child.name: isAutoCreated
child.description:
If the value of this attribute is TRUE, then the type of NetworkAddress identified in this object's typeOfNetworkAddress attribute is automatically created when the associated DeviceInterface is created. If the value of this attribute is FALSE, then the type of NetworkAddress identified in this object's typeOfNetworkAddress attribute is NOT automatically created when the associated DeviceInterface is created.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: isAutoCreated

child.name: typeOfNetworkAddress
child.description:
This is a string attribute, whose value contains the name of the subclass of NetworkAddress that is to be created. This attribute exists so that external systems can populate its value, thereby helping to automate the address creation task.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: typeOfNetworkAddress
